\title{small separator for a fibration}
\taxon{definition}

\import{frct-0000}


\p{Let #{E} be a cartesian fibration over #{B} such that #{B} has
binary products. A displayed object #{\bar{s}\in E\Sub{s}} is said to be a \em{small separator} for #{E} when any two vertical maps #{f,g:\bar{u}\DispTo{\Idn{x}}\bar{v}\in E\Sub{x}} are equal when they are [agree on #{\bar{s}}-figures](frct-002I).}